<paper id="1496815773"><title>Towards a Logical Reconstruction of Relational Database Theory</title><year>1984</year><authors><author org="University of British Columbia, #TAB#" id="2162621422">Raymond Reiter</author></authors><n_citation>552</n_citation><doc_type /><references><reference>119495920</reference><reference>1531263763</reference><reference>1766332311</reference><reference>1968915456</reference><reference>1970457902</reference><reference>1973644634</reference><reference>2003017562</reference><reference>2010013526</reference><reference>2011308078</reference><reference>2027750453</reference><reference>2031929451</reference><reference>2039601877</reference><reference>2059572526</reference><reference>2105486835</reference><reference>2122789628</reference><reference>2155322595</reference><reference>2165467455</reference><reference>2945259913</reference></references><venue id="" type="">On Conceptual Modelling (Intervale)</venue><doi>10.1007/978-1-4612-5196-5_8</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.43639">Data mining</keyword><keyword weight="0.59127">Conjunctive query</keyword><keyword weight="0.60263">Database model</keyword><keyword weight="0.60899">View</keyword><keyword weight="0.45735">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.60472">Database design</keyword><keyword weight="0.58577">Database schema</keyword><keyword weight="0.63405">Database theory</keyword><keyword weight="0.59547">Relational model</keyword><keyword weight="0.40775">Mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.58144">Probabilistic database</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, New York, NY</publisher><abstract>Insofar as database theory can be said to owe a debt to logic, the currency on loan is model theoretic in the sense that a database can be viewed as a particular kind of first order interpretation, and query evaluation is a process of truth functional evaluation of first order formulae with respect, to this interpretation. It is this model theoretic paradigm which leads, for example, to many valued propositional logics for databases with null values.</abstract></paper>